import subprocess
import sys

# We'll run multiple test cases by providing input and capturing output
TESTS = [
    # Sample 1
    ("3\ntakahashi 2\naoki 6\nsnuke 5\n", "snuke\n"),
    # N = 1
    ("1\nabc 100\n", "abc\n"),
    # lexicographic order ties on prefixes
    ("3\na 1\nab 2\naba 3\n", "aba\n"),
    # larger ratings
    ("4\nzz 10\naa 20\nmm 30\nbb 40\n", "zz\n"),
    # ratings sum exactly multiple of n -> index 0
    ("3\nalpha 1\nbeta 2\ngamma 3\n", "alpha\n"),
    # random check
    ("5\ndelta 1\necho 2\nbravo 3\ncharlie 4\nfoxtrot 5\n", "echo\n"),
]

solution = sys.executable + " solution.py"

failures = []
for i, (inp, expected) in enumerate(TESTS, 1):
    p = subprocess.Popen([sys.executable, "solution.py"], stdin=subprocess.PIPE, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE, text=True)
    out, err = p.communicate(inp)
    if out != expected:
        failures.append((i, inp, expected, out, err))

if failures:
    print("FAILURES:")
    for f in failures:
        i, inp, expected, out, err = f
        print(f"Test {i} failed")
        print("Input:")
        print(inp)
        print("Expected:")
        print(expected)
        print("Got:")
        print(out)
        print("Err:")
        print(err)
    sys.exit(1)
else:
    print("All tests passed")
